HEADWORD: Si
<hw>Si</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A
syllable applied, in solmization, to the note B; more recently, to the
seventh tone of any major diatonic scale. It was added to Guido's scale
by Le Maire about the end of the 17th century.</def><-- now called ti
-->⟦br⟧
